    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A Belgian variation of Art Nouveau, so-called after the exhibition of the same name, which was organized by lawyer Octave Maus in 1893. The term is often used in conjunction with "Les Style des Vingt," as that group was its predecessor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
